## Summary

Implements agent-scoped Policy overlays under `scopes.agents.<agentId>` for the policy sections whose evidence is already attributable to a named agent: `tools` and `agents.workspace`.

The overlay model is additive: top-level `tools.*` and `agents.workspace` claims still run, while `scopes.agents.<agentId>.tools` and `scopes.agents.<agentId>.agents.workspace` can add stricter named-agent claims and emit their own findings against the same observed config.

This uses a generic scoped container instead of a per-agent mini-grammar, so future sections such as sandbox and ingress can join the same shape after their PRs land and their evidence carries agent identity. Unsupported scoped sections and unsupported scoped `tools` keys are rejected rather than silently ignored.

`tools.alsoAllow.expected` is supported as an exact-list conformance claim. It reports missing expected additive grants and unexpected extra additive grants, including the empty-list case where policy expects no `alsoAllow` entries.

Example:

```jsonc
{
  "tools": {
    "exec": { "allowHosts": ["gateway", "sandbox"] },
    "alsoAllow": { "expected": [] }
  },
  "agents": {
    "workspace": { "allowedAccess": ["none", "ro"] }
  },
  "scopes": {
    "agents": {
      "lobster-node": {
        "agents": {
          "workspace": { "allowedAccess": ["rw"] }
        },
        "tools": {
          "exec": { "allowHosts": ["node"] },
          "alsoAllow": { "expected": ["lobster"] }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}
```

## Verification

- `pnpm docs:list`
- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1 docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.ts extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts`
- `pnpm docs:check-mdx docs/cli/policy.md docs/plugins/reference/policy.md docs/plan/policy-agent-scoped-overlays.md`
- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/policy/src/doctor/register.test.ts extensions/policy/src/cli.test.ts -- --reporter=dot`
- `git diff --check`
- `codex review --base origin/main`

## Real behavior proof

Behavior addressed: Policy conformance can now express stricter workspace and tool posture claims for a named agent without weakening deployment-wide policy claims.
Real environment tested: WSL checkout at `/root/src/openclaw-policy-agent-scoped-design` on Ubuntu-24.04.
Exact steps or command run after this patch: Ran docs listing, MDX validation, Markdown formatting, whitespace checks, focused Policy plugin doctor/CLI tests, and Codex branch review against `origin/main`.
Evidence after fix: Policy shape validation accepts `scopes.agents.<agentId>.tools` and `scopes.agents.<agentId>.agents.workspace`; unsupported scoped sections are rejected; policy findings for scoped overlays match normalized agent ids and apply `main` overlays to implicit default-agent posture when there is no explicit agent list; `tools.alsoAllow.expected` reports missing and unexpected additive grants.
Observed result after fix: 169 focused Vitest tests pass; docs checks, formatting checks, whitespace checks, and Codex review pass with no accepted/actionable findings. Codex review's own read-only sandbox could not run Vitest because Vite tried to write `node_modules/.vite-temp`, so the WSL test command above is the test proof.
What was not tested: Full repository test suite; this change is scoped to Policy plugin conformance and policy docs.

